HEADWORD: Hygrometrical
<hw>Hy`gro*met"ric*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>hygrom⟦eacute⟧trique</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to hygrometry; made with, or according to, the hygrometer;
<as>as, <ex>hygrometric</ex> observations</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Readily absorbing and retaining moisture; <as>as,
<ex>hygrometric</ex> substances, like potash</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hygrometry</ent>⟦br⟧
